---

## 1️⃣ Allowed Use (Permitted)

- **Personal Use:** Protecting your child and family by checking batch codes against official recall data.
- **Community Sharing:** Sharing this tool and its verified links with other parents for public safety.
- **Adaptation:** Improving the tool's interface or features for non-commercial safety purposes.
- **Attribution:** You must give appropriate credit to **"TechDadShanghai / SafeFeed Action"**.

## 2️⃣ Prohibited Use (Non-Commercial Only)

**Commercial use is strictly prohibited. This project is a volunteer-led non-profit community utility.** You may NOT:

- **Sell or charge** for access to this tool, its database (`recall_database.csv`), or derived results.
- **Incorporate** content into a paid subscription, paid course, membership program, or "Premium" safety alert service.
- **Indirect Monetization:** Republish as your own work for direct or indirect monetization.

Any commercial exploitation of this project's database or code constitutes a license violation.

## 3️⃣ Official Access & Integrity

Always access the most accurate and officially verified version via the primary channels:
- **GitHub Repository:** [https://github.com/MilesXLab/safefeed-action](https://github.com/MilesXLab/safefeed-action)
- **Live Search Tool:** [https://milesxlab.github.io/safefeed-action/](https://milesxlab.github.io/safefeed-action/)

This tool consolidates data from over 20+ global regulatory bodies (FSA, FSAI, AGES, FDA, etc.). Cloned copies or third-party mirrors may contain outdated or unverified information.

## 4️⃣ Security & Support

- **Report Issues:** Found outdated info or new recall data? Report via [GitHub Issues](https://github.com/MilesXLab/safefeed-action/issues).
- **Safety Alert:** If anyone charges you for this information, please REJECT and REPORT it immediately.
- **Contact:** For non-profit partnerships or volunteer inquiries: miles.x.dev@outlook.com

